					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Records the grant by Queen <hi rend="bold">Vasantipōṟi-Chōḻamahādēvi</hi> to Vasantīśvara (?) of three hundred <hi rend="italic">maṟutus</hi> of land and two gardens in <hi rend="bold">Viripaṟiti</hi> for the merit of <hi rend="bold">Puṇyakumāra-Pṛithivī-Vallabha-Chōḻamahārāja.</hi> It also says that twelve <hi rend="italic">maṟutus</hi> of land were given to a certain <hi rend="bold">Vānapōtula Muchchiya,</hi> who was to render service to the devotees <hi rend="italic">(tapasulu)</hi> attached to the temple (?)</p>						

						</summary>
